JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 84
IS  - 3
SP  - 1238
EP  - 1263
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This article studies the non-parametric identification and estimation of voters’ preferences when voters are ideological. We establish that voter preference distributions and other parameters of interest can be identified from aggregate electoral data. We also show that these objects can be consistently estimated and illustrate our analysis by performing an actual estimation using data from the 1999 European Parliament elections.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdw046
